---
export interface Props {
  showWaterIngress?: boolean;
  showHydrostatic?: boolean;
  showFloorDrains?: boolean;
}

const { 
  showWaterIngress = true, 
  showHydrostatic = true,
  showFloorDrains = true
} = Astro.props;
---

<div class="nbc-floor-drainage bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center">
    <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">🌊</span>
    NBC 9.16.3 Floor-on-Ground Drainage Requirements
  </h3>

  <div class="bg-cyan-50 border-l-4 border-cyan-500 p-4 mb-6">
    <p class="text-sm">
      <strong>Critical:</strong> Unless proven unnecessary, grading or drainage is required to prevent water ingress. 
      Where groundwater causes hydrostatic pressure beneath floors, structural concrete slabs designed to resist 
      these pressures are mandatory.
    </p>
  </div>

  {showWaterIngress && (
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-700">9.16.3.1 Control of Water Ingress</h4>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Requirements</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Grading to direct water away</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Drainage to intercept groundwater</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Remove water before slab contact</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Prevent moisture migration</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Problems Prevented</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
              <span>Window condensation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
              <span>Mold and mildew growth</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
              <span>Flooring damage</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">⚠️</span>
              <span>Structural deterioration</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-cyan-50 rounded">
        <p class="text-xs">
          <strong>Methods:</strong> Perimeter drains, underslab drainage, granular layers, 
          sump pits, proper site grading
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  {showHydrostatic && (
    <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-red-700">9.16.3.2 Hydrostatic Pressure</h4>
      
      <div class="mb-4">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">
          When groundwater rises above floor level, upward hydrostatic pressure can cause slabs to heave, 
          crack, or wooden floors to float. Structural design per NBC Part 4 required.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Design Requirements</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">!</span>
              <span>NBC Part 4 structural design</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">!</span>
              <span>Calculate uplift forces</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">!</span>
              <span>Reinforced concrete slab</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-red-600 mr-2">!</span>
              <span>Engineer certification required</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded">
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-2 text-sm">Pressure Calculation</h5>
          <div class="text-xs space-y-1">
            <p><strong>Formula:</strong> P = ρ × g × h</p>
            <p>• P = Pressure (kPa)</p>
            <p>• ρ = 1000 kg/m³ (water)</p>
            <p>• g = 9.81 m/s²</p>
            <p>• h = Height above floor (m)</p>
            <div class="mt-2 pt-2 border-t">
              <p><strong>Example:</strong> 0.5m water = 4.9 kPa uplift</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-4 p-3 bg-red-100 rounded">
        <p class="text-xs">
          <strong>Critical:</strong> If water table >200mm above slab, upward pressure exceeds typical 
          slab weight. Special design required.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  {showFloorDrains && (
    <div class="bg-cyan-50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
      <h4 class="font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-700">9.16.3.3 Floor Drains</h4>
      
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Requirements</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Slope floors to drains</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Minimum 1% slope (10mm/m)</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>No water accumulation</span>
            </li>
            <li class="flex items-start">
              <span class="text-cyan-600 mr-2">✓</span>
              <span>Connect to approved disposal</span>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h5 class="font-semibold mb-3">Installation Details</h5>
          <ul class="text-sm space-y-2">
            <li>• Located at low points</li>
            <li>• P-trap for sewer gases</li>
            <li>• Backwater valve if needed</li>
            <li>• Regular maintenance access</li>
            <li>• NBC 9.31.4.3 compliance</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  )}

  <!-- Solutions Summary -->
  <div class="bg-amber-50 rounded-lg p-6">
    <h4 class="font-bold mb-4">Comprehensive Floor Drainage Solutions</h4>
    
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-center">
      <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-1">📐</div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold">Site Grading</div>
        <div class="text-xs">5% slope away</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-1">💧</div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold">Underslab Drainage</div>
        <div class="text-xs">Granular layer</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-1">🔧</div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold">Perimeter Drains</div>
        <div class="text-xs">Weeping tile</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-1">⚡</div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold">Sump System</div>
        <div class="text-xs">Active pumping</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-1">🛡️</div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold">Vapor Barrier</div>
        <div class="text-xs">6 mil poly min</div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-3 rounded">
        <div class="text-2xl mb-1">🏗️</div>
        <div class="text-xs font-semibold">Structural Slab</div>
        <div class="text-xs">If hydrostatic</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-6 text-xs text-slate-500 border-t pt-3">
    <p><strong>Reference:</strong> NBC 2015 Part 9, Section 9.16.3 - Drainage</p>
    <p>Proper floor drainage prevents moisture problems and structural damage from hydrostatic pressure.</p>
  </div>
</div>